Date:6/15/2004 8:33:28 PM
From:Stewart Whitman
I wrote a scanner to calculate Piotroski scores and ran a few indices through
it. I put the results on the web here:

http://members.cox.net/econisvoodoo/piotroski/

The scans are without regard to valuation (unless the index itself claims some
bias). I wrote the tool to scan individual stocks and it's been a really handy
when testing people's recommendations from articles - I usually eliminate low
scorers quickly unless there are some very specific reasons to buy. I started
running it on indices and I saw some interesting companies recommended here
that top the list.

The Russell 3000 is the most interesting general index (the list for this index
is somewhat outdated though). I'm still looking for better sources for more
indices.

Stew
